  "response": "Cricket's dominance in India is complex. While it has significantly overshadowed other sports, it hasn't completely \"killed\" them. Here are some key points:\n\nPros of Cricket's Dominance:\n1. Massive popularity and viewership\n2. Significant financial investments\n3. Professional leagues like IPL\n4. International success and recognition\n5. Economic opportunities for players\n\nChallenges for Other Sports:\n1. Limited media coverage\n2. Less funding and sponsorship\n3. Lower public interest\n4. Fewer infrastructure and training facilities\n5. Reduced opportunities for athletes\n\nRecent Positive Developments:\n1. Growing interest in sports like kabaddi\n2. Improved performance in Olympic sports\n3. Success of athletes in badminton, wrestling, boxing\n4. Government initiatives to support other sports\n5. Emerging professional leagues in various sports\n\nWhile cricket remains dominant, other sports are gradually gaining ground and receiving more attention. The situation is improving, but cricket still holds a significant advantage in terms of popularity and resources.\n\nThe sports ecosystem is evolving, and efforts are being made to diversify and support multiple sports in India.",
